column16: Copper Artwork in Metal Frame by Local Artist Jack Eggman 35 x 48
column17: Celebrate the vision of  Jack Eggman, acclaimed Tucson artist , with this extraordinary original art piece. Jack Eggman, a third generation Arizonian descended from copper miners, transformed his heritage into art by pioneering copper-inlaid monotypes - a medium that unites the raw power of primal art with the structural elegance of cubism . Each piece reflects both his personal story and Tucson's cultural roots, resulting in work that is as meaningful as it is visually striking. This is a rare opportunity to acquire a one-of-a-kind piece from a contemporary artist whose vision and craftsmanship continue to inspire and captivate.

column16: Copper Artwork in Metal Frame by Local Artist Jack Eggman 32 x 43 (horizontal piece)
column17:
Jack Eggman is a highly skilled artist from Southern Arizona who brings a unique and personal touch to his artwork by incorporating copper into his pieces. This distinctive element adds a rich and dynamic texture to his creations, giving them an added layer of depth and character.

What makes Jack Eggman's use of copper even more special is the connection to his family's history. His past generations worked in the copper mines of Southern Arizona, creating a deep-rooted tie to the material and its significance in his art. Through his work, Eggman pays homage to his heritage and carries on a tradition that is both meaningful and visually stunning.

By owning a piece of Jack Eggman's art, you not only get to enjoy a beautifully crafted and visually striking piece, but you also get to own a piece of history and a connection to the artist's unique family legacy. Don't miss the opportunity to own this 33 x 44 metal framed artwork that is not only visually captivating but holds a deep and personal story behind it.

In the center of the composition, a donkey is shown with a cat on his back, symbolizing love and connection.

The figures are surrounded by swirling patterns and abstract shapes, adding depth and movement to the artwork. The overall feeling of the piece is one of joy and contentment, reminding the viewer to cherish the relationships and connections in their life.

Peo's use of mixed media techniques, including bold brush strokes and intricate details, adds texture and visual interest to the piece. "Love the One You're With" is a beautiful and thought-provoking artwork that celebrates the beauty of love and human connection.

Donated by Brenda Peo.
